46:08.133 --> 46:09.434
In the early 1960s,

46:09.500 --> 46:13.338
Enzo Ferrari's cars
ruled sports-car racing,

46:13.404 --> 46:14.940
Le Mans especially.

46:15.006 --> 46:16.307
At the start of the decade,

46:16.374 --> 46:18.977
he had won the famous
and gruelling 24-hour race

46:19.044 --> 46:21.412
three times on the trot.

46:21.479 --> 46:25.583
However, the company was in
deep financial difficulty,

46:25.650 --> 46:28.854
so when Ford offered to buy
the entire business,

46:28.854 --> 46:30.889
